 The All Progressives Congress has cancelled a purported emergency NEC meeting fixed for Thursday, March 17. A terse statement by the party’s National Secretary, Send James Akpanudoedehe on Wednesday night quoted the party’s chairman as giving the directive. “As directed by the National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Caretaker/Extraordinary Convention Planning (CECPC) and Governor of Yobe State, H.E. Mai Mala Buni, a purported emergency meeting of the  Party’s National Executive Committee (NEC) slated for Thursday, March 17, 2022 is hereby cancelled.” 